.TP 2
.B
\\011:
is always a tab
.TP 2
.B
\\0113:
is a tab followed by the character "3"
.TP 2
.B
\\113:
might be a back reference, otherwise the character with octal code 113
.TP 2
.B
\\377:
might be a back reference, otherwise the byte consisting entirely of 1 bits
.TP 2
.B
